pull.title: Fix addrman crashes
pull.body:
A function returned the element to remove from a bucket, instead of its position in that bucket. This function was only called when a tried bucket overflowed, which only happens after many outgoing connections have been made.

Closes: #1065, #1156

events.body: This has survived about 10 hours of running inside valgrind here on a node that previously crashed and with some tweaks to make it more likely to crash. It also survived a new node bringup. The code looks okay to me, so I'm going to go ahead and pull it in the hopes of getting more people testing it on master.
